# vvaharness — Qwen3.6 (36B MoE, thinking) large-context variant.
#
# WHY: Ollama's runtime num_ctx defaults to ~4k regardless of the model's
# 262144 native capability, and the OpenAI /v1 endpoint can't set it per
# request — so it must be baked in here, same as the 14B variant.
#
# BUILD:
#   ollama create qwen3.6-36b-128k -f ./Modelfile.qwen3.6
# Then point the Model-B benchmark runs at it:
#   OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen3.6-36b-128k  +  --config ./config.qwen3.6.yaml
# (Name matches the num_ctx below. If you raise num_ctx to 262144, rebuild as
#  qwen3.6-36b-256k so the label stays honest.)
#
# ⚠ RAM/VRAM: a 36B MoE at a huge num_ctx allocates a very large KV cache
# (tens of GB). 131072 (128k) is the default below as a practical "max". If the
# model OOMs or eval crawls, lower to 65536; if you have the headroom and want
# the true native max, raise to 262144 AND bump the budgets in
# config.qwen3.6.yaml to match. Keep (chunk_token_budget + max output) < num_ctx.

FROM qwen3.6

PARAMETER num_ctx 131072
PARAMETER temperature 0.2
